      <scopecontent id="aspace_8d71d4c7649701db99b67197b80b0ec5">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Letters to Stephen McKenna consists of social and literary letters addressed to the English novelist. The papers span the dates 1917-1939 and correspondents include Alfred Austin, Augustine Birrell, John Drinkwater, John Galsworthy, Compton Mackenzie, Arthur Wing Pinero, John Sargeaunt, and Frank Swinnerton. Many of the notes concern dinner invitations and other social engagements.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
